ComicInfo.Summary:
Young Conan breaks into the fabled Tower of the Elephant in order to steal the gem known as the Heart of the Elephant. Inside, he finds a noble creature ensnared by the evil sorcerer Yara.
Conan and a crew of Zingaran freebooters battle the Black Giants.
Conan joins a group of Zingaran Freebooters who sail west until they find a mysterious island.
Amalric rescues Lissa returns her to her desert city.
Conan and Natala escape from Xuthal.
Natala is kidnapped by Thalis, but Thalis is eaten by Thog.
Conan and Natala wander into the city of Xuthal from the desert and find it almost deserted except for sleeping men and a shadowy demon.
Conan frees Yasmina from the Black Seers but is unable to keep her for long.
Conan, Kerim Shah, and his men battle the acolytes of the Black Seers.
Yasmina awakes to find she has been captured by the Master of Yimsha.
Conan learns that the Afguli clans have turned on him, so he plans to rescue Yasmina alone but is joined by Kerim Shah and his men who agree to join Conan.
9,500 B.C.: The Aquilonian empire has fallen and the Hyrkanian horde ravages the world. The coming ice age drives the nothern tribes south. Yet another global cataclysm reshapes the continents to their current forms.
Conan and Yasmina flee the Wazulis and are attacked by Khemsa and Gitara. During the battle, four wizards appear and take their revenge on Khemsa and take Yasmina from Conan.
When Yar Afzal is killed by Khemsa's sorcery, Conan and Yasmina must flee the Wazuli camp.
Conan and Yasmina reach the Zhaibar Pass and meet up with Yar Afzal.
Conan kidnaps Yasmina.
Gitara and Khemsa betray Kerim Shah and plan to use the information of the kidnapped Yasmina to their own ends.
Sorcerers are killing Yasmina's brother, Bhunda Chand, the King of Vendhya.
Conan must battle both Jehungir Agha and Khosatral Khel to escape the island Xapur.
Conan finds a city on the island of Xapur where only ruins stood weeks before and learns of the rising of Khosatral Khel.
Jehungir and Ghaznavi plot to use Octavia to trap Conan on the island Xapur. Unknown to them, a fisherman has awoken an ancient warrior on the same island.
After being attacked by cannibals, Conan rescues Zabibi and ends up assisting her in her search for the magical ring called the Star of Khorala.
Conan and Fafnir fulfill the prophecy of Bal-Sagoth, which leads to the destruction of the island and all its people.
Conan and Fafnir the Vanir are stranded on the ancient island of Bal-Sagoth in the Vilayet Sea. At first they are enemies, but they quickly decide to co-operate in order to survive. They rescue a girl, Kyrie, and fight the high priest Gothan in order to restore her as goddess and queen Aala of Bal-Sagoth.
